The '''Cadí-Moixeró Natural Park''' ({{lang-ca|Parc Natural del Cadí-Moixeró}}) is a [[natural park (Spain)|natural park]] to the north of [[Catalonia]], [[Spain]], near the border with [[Andorra]]. The park was established in 1983 and encompasses {{convert|41060|ha}} of mountainous terrain in the [[comarca|comarques]] of [[Alt Urgell]], [[Berguedà]] and [[Cerdanya (comarca)|Cerdanya]]. It stretches for more than 30 kilometers over the [[mountain range]]s of [[Serra del Cadí]] and [[Serra de Moixeró]], with [[Vulturó]] standing at {{convert|2648|m}} as its highest point.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://parcsnaturals.gencat.cat/web/.content/home/cadi_moixero/coneixeu_nos/centre_de_documentacio/fons_documental/biblioteca_digital/turisme/parque_natural_del_cadi-moixero/pncm_cast.pdf|title=El Cadí-Moixeró Natural Park (in Spanish)|author=|first=|date=|work=Generalitat de Catalunya|publisher=Gencat.cat|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|accessdate=August 29, 2017}}</ref>

