'''Enderby Plain''' (also known as '''Enderby Abyssal Plain''' or '''East Abyssal Plain''') ({{coord|60|S|40|E|source:GNIS|display=inline,title}}) is an undersea plain (or ''[[abyssal plain]]''), located off the coast of [[Enderby Land]] and [[Queen Maud Land]], [[East Antarctica]]. The name was approved by the [[U.S. Board on Geographic Names]] [[Advisory Committee on Undersea Features]] in June 1988.<ref name=gnis/>

This submarine terrain feature is named after the [[Samuel Enderby & Sons|Enderby Brothers]], owners of a 19th-century [[whaling]] company based in [[London, England]]. The company sponsored several expeditions to [[Antarctica]] in the mid-19th century.

