'''Kattendijk Sands''' is a five million years old marine geological formation north of [[Antwerp]], [[Belgium]]. including the north-western parts of the [[Campine]] region.
The area was named by De Heuter and Laga in 1976.<ref name="Schittekat"> {{cite book | last = Schittekat | first = J. | chapter = Engineering geology of the Boom clay in the Antwerp area | title = Screw Piles&nbsp;— Installation and Design in Stiff Clay | editor-last = Holeyman | editor-first = Alain E. | publisher = Taylor & Francis | year = 2001 | url = https://books.google.com/books?id=o_HpfZ2MFAgC&pg=PA11 | isbn = 9789058091925}}</ref> The [[sand]]s range from medium fine to coarse and contain a large proportion of shell grit.<ref>{{Cite book | editor-last = van der Sijp | editor-first = Jaap Willem Charles Marie | title = New aspects of mineral and water resources in The Netherlands | publisher = M. Nijhoff | location = The Hague | year = 1973 | oclc = 2367071 | url = https://books.google.com/books?id=uqvkAAAAMAAJ&q=%22Kattendijk+Sands%22&dq=%22Kattendijk+Sands}}</ref>
==Geology== The clay of the [[Rupelian]] era developed to a depth of approximately {{convert|70|m|abbr=on}} beneath a deposit of [[Neogene]] sand.<ref name="Schittekat"/> The formation has a [[Miocene]] Era [[aquifer]], while the clay level dates to the [[Pliocene]].<ref>{{Cite book | last1 = Coetsiers | first1 = M. | last2 = Walraevens | first2 =K. | chapter = The Neogene Aquifer, Flanders, Belgium | editor1-last = Edmunds | editor1-first = W. Mike | editor2-last = Shand | editor2-first = Paul | title = Natural groundwater quality | url = https://books.google.com/books?id=FXmhyFYZmHIC&pg=PA268&lpg=PA268&dq=Kattendijk+Sands | publisher = John Wiley & Sons | year = 2009 | isbn = 9781444300352}}</ref>
==Palaeontology== A Pliocene species of [[auk]] (''Alca stewarti'') was found in 2000.<ref>{{Cite journal | last1 = Martin | first1 = J.W.R. | last2 = Walker | first2 = C.A. | last3 = Bonser | first3 = R. | last4 = Dyke | first4 = Gareth J. | title = A new species of large auk from the Pliocene of Belgium | journal = Oryctos | year = 2000 | volume = 3 | pages = 53–60 | url = http://eprints.soton.ac.uk/205319/ | accessdate =4 November 2012 }}</ref>
