The {{nihongo|'''Science Museum of Map and Survey'''|地図と測量の科学館|Chizu to Sokuryō no Kagakukan}} is a museum in [[Tsukuba, Ibaraki]], [[Japan]] that is dedicated to [[Cartography|mapping]] and [[surveying]].
The museum was the first of its kind in Japan when it was opened by the [[Geographical Survey Institute of Japan]] in June 1996.
