{{Japan-museum-stub}}

'''The Phallus''' is a rock formation (pillar) in [[Grand County, Utah]], in the [[United States]].<ref>{{GNIS|1436120}}</ref> It is within the [[Arches National Park]].<ref>{{cite book|last=Bjornstad|first=Eric|title=Desert Rock I: Rock Climbs in the National Parks|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=CtiKwHPLrC0C&pg=PA149|date=1 January 1996|publisher=Globe Pequot Press|isbn=978-0-934641-92-0|page=149}}</ref>

The Phallus stands {{convert|100|ft}} tall, and was named from the fact it resembles a [[phallus]].<ref name="Green2012">{{cite book|last=Green|first=Stewart M.|title=Rock Climbing Utah|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=27dxgNjPFpEC&pg=PA25|date=18 December 2012|publisher=Rowman & Littlefield|isbn=978-0-7627-9284-9|page=25}}</ref> A climbing route has been published in guidebooks.<ref name="Green2012" />

